      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DANCING DENNIS (1) was well supported last time and gave a sight after a fast early split but could manage only the minor money, finishing a 3.5 lengths second (16.00) over 275m at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Rates highly and will give a great sight. TOO BUSY (8) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (23.09) last time in a Grade 5 at Mandurah. Solid winning record at this trip. Cannot be taken lightly. CHEDDAR MONELLI (2) had been racing well prior to his last start sixth at this track following a Grade 5 win three back with a third placing. Rates a winning chance on best. NED (6) is a last start winner who can measure up again.",
